Popular terrorism focuses on harming civilians and aims to undermine the sense of security necessary to lead a normal life of a civilian population.
The severe wave of attacks that took place this year, with attacks in Be 'er Sheva, Hadera, Bnei Brak, Ariel, Elad, and especially the one that took place in early April on the busy Dizengoff Street in the heart of Tel Aviv, by a terrorist who was assimilated into a crowd, led the police to think creatively in order to develop a tool that could be used to train fighters to storm terrorists within the civilian population.
